Create: This commit is created my practice Bitcoin.
Initialize project using Create React App
upgrade solidity version and add openzeppelin
Update user subscription swapping and card updating feature
Update and fix broken class imports in SubscriptionController
Update gateway id field to be unique in plans table
Update missing imports in database config file
Update database config file keys and values
Update and fix asset bundling to working condition
Update user factory password field to use hashed value
Update public index.php to handle maintenance mode correctly
Update readme to reflect installation and usage changes
Update multi-tenancy functionality and remove previously built-in features
Rework and upgrade project to Laravel 9

Add Console Commands

Created console commands to extend the default commands; to match the new folder structure

Update DomainPolicyMakeCommand.php

Updated the command to extend the default PolicyMakeCommand

Update DomainControllerMakeCommand.php

Renamed and updated the command to extend the default ControllerMakeCommand

Update README.md

Add Admin root setup steps
Add custom commands sub section under usage section

Update package.json

Update npm package versions

Update ConfirmationToken and TwoFactor models boot methods

Fix the boot methods to call the parent boot

Add alternative tenant switch functionality

Add tenant switch controller which switches and logs user's access timestamp company
Add alternative switch routes
Add alternative attribute to User model
Add alternative switch functionality to Tenant middleware

Add Tenancy (company) events and listeners

Add company user login event to handle user login event
Add company user event subscriber to handle all company user events
Register company user event subscriber
in event service provider

Add Tenancy related config file, trait and migration

Tenancy config file used to hold multi-tenancy settings and credentials
HasTenancy trait used to dynamically handle user-tenant relationship
Migration adds last login colomn to tenancy (company) users table

Add Role based Artisan Commands

Add assign user role command
Add create permission command

Update Role Table Seeder

Add browse admin permission

Update Permissions Service Provider

Add try catch block to catch exception if no database connection available

Add webpack livereload plugin

Used to check and reload page on assets change

Add Force HTTPS configuration

Added url scheme service provider to force HTTPS on assets based on config
Updated .env.example to include 'FORCE_HTTPS' config
Updated README.md

Update ViewComposers

Fix UserCompaniesComposer; Add Auth check before fetching companies

Update README.md

Add Single Database Multi-tenancy usage instructions

Update Single Database Multi-tenancy Functionality

Fix TenantScope to dynamically get the 'tenant' foreign key
Fix ForTenants trait by adding a check before adding the TenantScope and TenantObserver
Move 'WithoutForTenants' scope from Project model to ForTenants Trait to make it accessible in any model that calls ForTenants trait

Add Single Database Multi-tenancy Feature

Added functionality for a single database multi-tenancy

Update Permission Service Provider

Fix service provider by checking if permission (model) table exists

Add README.md

Added details of the project

BUG FIX: provide nil check in `Transaction#block_number`

* **BUG:** calling `#block_number` on a transaction that has just been
  committed to the blockchain causes `Utility#from_hex` to raise an
  argument error exception
* **CAUSE:** because the transaction is new, its `blockNumber` value is
  `nil`, thus when I try to call `from_hex` `#to_i` is called on
  `nil`, which fails
* **FIX:** provide a nil check in `Transaction#block_number` to avoid
  calling `Utility#from_hex` if `blockNumber` is nil

NOTE:
* I have confirmed that this works locally, but have not provided a
  test for the patch, as the test harness for the project appears to
  be skeletal at the moment. Happy to provide one with guidance from
  upstream folks if the lack of testing is a blocker to merging.

Correct ID variable - tokenId should be itemId

NFTs objects should have itemId propriety and not tokenId propriety.
Creating a token but not listing it will defer the itemId and tokenId, fetching the marketplace based on tokenId will result in the wrong token being fetched.

For example, you might have created 18 tokens (tokenId.last = 18), but listed only 5. The 4th tokenId will not correspond to the 4th itemId.

BUG FIX: provide nil check in `Transaction#block_number`

* **BUG:** calling `#block_number` on a transaction that has just been
  committed to the blockchain causes `Utility#from_hex` to raise an
  argument error exception
* **CAUSE:** because the transaction is new, its `blockNumber` value is
  `nil`, thus when I try to call `from_hex` `#to_i` is called on
  `nil`, which fails
* **FIX:** provide a nil check in `Transaction#block_number` to avoid
  calling `Utility#from_hex` if `blockNumber` is nil

NOTE:
* I have confirmed that this works locally, but have not provided a
  test for the patch, as the test harness for the project appears to
  be skeletal at the moment. Happy to provide one with guidance from
  upstream folks if the lack of testing is a blocker to merging.
